revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{ombox
|type=content
|text=The ''[[Online Etymology Dictionary]]'' is a [[WP:SPS|self-published source]] and therefore editors consider it [[WP:QUESTIONABLE|non-reliable]]. It is recommended to use peer-reviewed scholarly works such as the ''[[Oxford English Dictionary]]'' instead. {{small|(See [[Wikipedia:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 306#etymonline|this archived discussion at the reliable sources noticeboard]]. {{tl|Cite OED}} can be used to cite the Oxford English Dictionary.)}}
}}

Produces a cited reference to the ''[[Online Etymology Dictionary]]'' website for the specified word(s). To specify the date of retrieval, use the optional <code>accessdate</code> parameter with an [[ISO 8601]] YYYY-MM-DD formatted date. 

'''Example:''' <code><nowiki>{{OEtymD|camouflage|accessdate=</nowiki>{{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}}<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code> produces:
:{{OEtymD|camouflage|accessdate={{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}}}}
'''Example 2:''' <code><nowiki>{{OEtymD|camouflage|name-list-style=vanc|accessdate=</nowiki>{{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}}<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code> produces:
:{{OEtymD|camouflage|name-list-style=vanc|accessdate={{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}}}}

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
[[Category:Dictionary source templates]]
}}</includeonly>

